Structs/ToneAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.name: documentTone
Structs/ToneAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.abstract: An object of type DocumentAnalysis that provides the results of the analysis for the full input document.

Structs/ToneAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.name: sentencesTone
Structs/ToneAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.abstract: An array of SentenceAnalysis objects that provides the results of the analysis for the individual sentences of the input content. The service returns results only for the first 100 sentences of the input. The field is omitted if the sentences parameter of the request is set to false.

Structs/ToneInput.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.name: text
Structs/ToneInput.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.abstract: The input content that the service is to analyze.

Structs/ToneChatInput.html#/s:14ToneAnal.name: utterances
Structs/ToneChatInput.html#/s:14ToneAnal.abstract: An array of Utterance objects that provides the input content that the service is to analyze.

Structs/UtteranceAnalysis.html#/s:14Tone.name: utteranceID
Structs/UtteranceAnalysis.html#/s:14Tone.abstract: The unique identifier of the utterance. The first utterance has ID 0, and the ID of each subsequent utterance is incremented by one.

Structs/UtteranceAnalysis.html#/s:14Tone.name: tones
Structs/UtteranceAnalysis.html#/s:14Tone.abstract: An array of ToneChatScore objects that provides results for the most prevalent tones of the utterance. The array includes results for any tone whose score is at least 0.5. The array is empty if no tone has a score that meets this threshold.

Structs/UtteranceAnalysis.html#/s:14Tone.name: error
Structs/UtteranceAnalysis.html#/s:14Tone.abstract: 2017-09-21:** An error message if the utterance contains more than 500 characters. The service does not analyze the utterance. 2016-05-19: Not returned.

Structs/ToneCategory.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.name: tones
Structs/ToneCategory.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.abstract: An array of ToneScore objects that provides the results for the tones of the category.

Structs/ToneCategory.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.name: categoryID
Structs/ToneCategory.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.abstract: The unique, non-localized identifier of the category for the results. The service can return results for the following category IDs: emotion_tone, language_tone, and social_tone.

Structs/ToneCategory.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.name: categoryName
Structs/ToneCategory.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.abstract: The user-visible, localized name of the category.

Structs/Utterance.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.name: text
Structs/Utterance.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.abstract: An utterance contributed by a user in the conversation that is to be analyzed. The utterance can contain multiple sentences.

Structs/Utterance.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.name: user
Structs/Utterance.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.abstract: A string that identifies the user who contributed the utterance specified by the text parameter.

Structs/UtteranceAnalyses.html#/s:14Tone.name: utterancesTone
Structs/UtteranceAnalyses.html#/s:14Tone.abstract: An array of UtteranceAnalysis objects that provides the results for each utterance of the input.

Structs/UtteranceAnalyses.html#/s:14Tone.name: warning
Structs/UtteranceAnalyses.html#/s:14Tone.abstract: 2017-09-21:** A warning message if the content contains more than 50 utterances. The service analyzes only the first 50 utterances. 2016-05-19: Not returned.

Structs/ToneScore.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.name: score
Structs/ToneScore.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.abstract: The score for the tone. * 2017-09-21: The score that is returned lies in the range of 0.5 to 1. A score greater than 0.75 indicates a high likelihood that the tone is perceived in the content. * 2016-05-19: The score that is returned lies in the range of 0 to 1. A score less than 0.5 indicates that the tone is unlikely to be perceived in the content; a score greater than 0.75 indicates a high likelihood that the tone is perceived.

Structs/ToneScore.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.name: toneID
Structs/ToneScore.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.abstract: The unique, non-localized identifier of the tone. * 2017-09-21: The service can return results for the following tone IDs: anger, fear, joy, and sadness (emotional tones); analytical, confident, and tentative (language tones). The service returns results only for tones whose scores meet a minimum threshold of 0.5. * 2016-05-19: The service can return results for the following tone IDs of the different categories: for the emotion category: anger, disgust, fear, joy, and sadness; for the language category: analytical, confident, and tentative; for the social category: openness_big5, conscientiousness_big5, extraversion_big5, agreeableness_big5, and emotional_range_big5. The service returns scores for all tones of a category, regardless of their values.

Structs/ToneScore.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.name: toneName
Structs/ToneScore.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzer.abstract: The user-visible, localized name of the tone.

Structs/DocumentAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.name: tones
Structs/DocumentAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.abstract: 2017-09-21:** An array of ToneScore objects that provides the results of the analysis for each qualifying tone of the document. The array includes results for any tone whose score is at least 0.5. The array is empty if no tone has a score that meets this threshold. 2016-05-19: Not returned.

Structs/DocumentAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.name: toneCategories
Structs/DocumentAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.abstract: 2017-09-21:** Not returned. 2016-05-19: An array of ToneCategory objects that provides the results of the tone analysis for the full document of the input content. The service returns results only for the tones specified with the tones parameter of the request.

Structs/DocumentAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.name: warning
Structs/DocumentAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.abstract: 2017-09-21:** A warning message if the overall content exceeds 128 KB or contains more than 1000 sentences. The service analyzes only the first 1000 sentences for document-level analysis and the first 100 sentences for sentence-level analysis. 2016-05-19: Not returned.

Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.name: sentenceID
Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.abstract: The unique identifier of a sentence of the input content. The first sentence has ID 0, and the ID of each subsequent sentence is incremented by one.

Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.name: tones
Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.abstract: 2017-09-21:** An array of ToneScore objects that provides the results of the analysis for each qualifying tone of the sentence. The array includes results for any tone whose score is at least 0.5. The array is empty if no tone has a score that meets this threshold. 2016-05-19: Not returned.

Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.name: toneCategories
Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.abstract: 2017-09-21:** Not returned. 2016-05-19: An array of ToneCategory objects that provides the results of the tone analysis for the sentence. The service returns results only for the tones specified with the tones parameter of the request.

Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.name: inputFrom
Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.abstract: 2017-09-21:** Not returned. 2016-05-19: The offset of the first character of the sentence in the overall input content.

Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.name: inputTo
Structs/SentenceAnalysis.html#/s:14ToneA.abstract: 2017-09-21:** Not returned. 2016-05-19: The offset of the last character of the sentence in the overall input content.

Structs/ToneChatScore.html#/s:14ToneAnal.name: score
Structs/ToneChatScore.html#/s:14ToneAnal.abstract: The score for the tone in the range of 0.5 to 1. A score greater than 0.75 indicates a high likelihood that the tone is perceived in the utterance.

Structs/ToneChatScore.html#/s:14ToneAnal.name: toneID
Structs/ToneChatScore.html#/s:14ToneAnal.abstract: The unique, non-localized identifier of the tone for the results. The service can return results for the following tone IDs: sad, frustrated, satisfied, excited, polite, impolite, and sympathetic. The service returns results only for tones whose scores meet a minimum threshold of 0.5.

Structs/ToneChatScore.html#/s:14ToneAnal.name: toneName
Structs/ToneChatScore.html#/s:14ToneAnal.abstract: The user-visible, localized name of the tone.

Enums/RestError.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzerV3.abstract: An HTTP error with a status code and description.

Enums/JSON.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzerV34JSON.abstract: A number value, represented as an integer.

Enums/JSON.html#/s:14ToneAnalyzerV34JSON.abstract: Convert this JSON value to a decodable type.

Enums/JSON.html.name: JSON
Enums/JSON.html.abstract: A JSON value (one of string, number, object, array, true, false, or null).

Enums/RestError.html.name: RestError
Enums/RestError.html.abstract: An error from processing a network request or response.

Classes/ToneAnalyzer.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.name: serviceURL
Classes/ToneAnalyzer.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.abstract: The base URL to use when contacting the service.

Classes/ToneAnalyzer.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.name: defaultHeaders
Classes/ToneAnalyzer.html#/s:14ToneAnaly.abstract: The default HTTP headers for all requests to the service.
